args: You look upset, Cleo. What is it?
When I awoke this morning, the cleaning,\nwashing, and cooking were already done.
Oh yes. In fact, I believe she's finishing\nthe dishes as we speak.
Cleoooo! The dishes are clean as a bean!\nWhaddya want me to do now?
Er, I think that's everything that needs—
Oh man, these windows are FILTHY!\nLemme just clean 'em here.
Hell, it's the least I can do what with\nya givin' me a place to crash and all.
*sigh* You really are a hard worker.
Yeah, I'm always doin' something when\nwe're plannin' a festival—so if I ain't\nbusy, I tend to get all jittery.
Yeah, but not in a bad way. I love it.
Hey, Princey! Lemme grab a bit'a\nyer mug for a second, yeah?
Aaaah ha ha ha! Guess a fancy napkin-\nuser like you ain't heard that one before.\n＂Lemme talk to ya a sec＂, is what it means.
I need your help with the festival...
Sounds great! Can't wait to see what ya\ncome up with for your stall!
You won't be disappointed—I will have\nonly my finest breads on display!
Boy, gettin' people to agree to set up\nstalls is WAY easier with you around.
Hell, I shoulda thought to drag royalty\naround with me years ago.
Er, thanks, I guess? Although I'm not\nreally DOING anything here...
You're the one explaining everything.\nAll I'm contributing is my support.
Trust me, you're a huge help.
Festivals belong to the place they're held.\nNo matter how hard we try, they ain't\ngonna be a success without local help.
So that's why we're going around\nnegotiating with the people here?
Yep. Honestly, folks are usually kinda wary\n'bout the idea of a festival at first.
But the people here LOVE ya!\nHell, they'd probably do cartwheels\nover hot coals if ya asked 'em to.
I'll probably not ask them to do that.\nStill, I guess I see my purpose now.
Glad to hear it! Now if you're done,\nwe got a lot more stops to make.
...C'mon. Ain't there SOME way\nI can change your mind?
I'm sorry, but we really can't afford to\nspend time on something like this.

I explained how much coin you're likely
to make by puttin' out a stall, yeah?
Plus, if this festival is a big success,
it'll help your sales in the future!
I would love to help, Your Highness,\nbut I'm afraid I truly cannot.
I cannot run my shop and prepare for a\nfestival at the same time—and if I shut\ndown, how will I recover those lost sales?
It might be hard for a prince to imagine,\nbut a day of work is a day that we eat.
We don't have the time to help with a\nfestival that might end up as a total bust.
All right, I get ya. Sorry for the headache.
Are you really giving up, Natalie?
Hey, we can't force folks to help.\nAnd even if we tried... Huh?
Terrible news, husband! Our boat was\njust taken away by the river's current!
What?! We need to get it back right now!
It's too late. It's already floated\na good distance downstream.
But...but how are we going to\ncatch our fish without a boat?
To get their damn boat back!
She just jumped into the river!
I can't believe you returned our boat...
I suppose all is well that ends well,\nbut that was dangerous, Natalie.\nWhat if the current had taken YOU?
Yeah, well, a gal never knows if she\ncan do somethin' until she tries.
But why did you help me when I\njust turned you down?
Your boat ain't got nothin' to do with the\nfestival. I was just bein' neighborly.
I mean, what kinda jerk would I be\nif I got a kick outta watchin' folks\nsuffer after they turned me down?
Er, miss? Perhaps I may have been a bit\nhasty with my original answer of ＂no.＂\nIs it too late to help with your festival?
I am taking a page from your book.
One never knows if they can do\nsomething until they try, yes?
We'd be thrilled for the help. Thank you.
We're going to treat this town to the\nfinest fish dishes they've ever had!
Now THAT'S what I wanna hear!
I'm glad that all worked out.
(Natalie said people were only helping\nbecause I was there asking them...)
(But I think her energy and enthusiasm\nhave much more to do with it.)
Let's keep it up! We're gonna need more\nhelpers to make this festival world-class!
